<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{title}}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css"> 
    
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.production.min.js"></script>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.production.min.js"></script>
    
    <script src="/java/home.js" defer></script>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Can I Recycle THAT?</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>Why This App?</h2>
            <p>
                Sometimes, it can be hard to figure out what you can recycle.
            </p>
            <div class="warning-box">
                <strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Under Utah Code, it's an infraction to put prohibited items in recycling bins. Infractions can result in a <span class="fine">fine of up to $750</span>.
            </div>
            <p>
                With this Web App, you can easily find out if an item is recyclable or not.
            </p>
            <div class="steps">
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Snap</strong> a picture of the item</li>
                    <li><strong>Upload</strong> it to the app</li>
                    <li><strong>Get</strong> instant feedback on how to dispose of it</li>
                </ol>
                <p style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.95rem;">The app uses machine learning to predict the waste type and provide disposal instructions.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
    <main>
        <div id="react-root"></div>
        
        {{{body}}}
    </main>
    
    <footer>
        <p>2026. No rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>